  "title": "Guidance: Re-render InfiniteHits based on time without calling search api",
  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe 🙏**\r\nI have an index that contains Restaurants where each restaurant has a specific open/close time and location which depending on the day of week/time in the object.  Depending on the time when the Restaurant object is rendered, it may appear in my results or not.  I'm looking for a way to re-render my current results as the time changes without making a new API call.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like 🤔**\r\nI want to re-render a Custom Component that is wrapped in the connectInfiniteHits without making an additional call to the Algolia API.\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered ✨**\r\nMy first reaction is to use a piece of state that is updated every minute that is used as part of the key in the render, but I think that would call the Algolia API to get more results\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nAdd any other context or screenshots about the feature request here.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI'm looking for guidance on how I would re-render a Custom Component using connectInfiniteHits.",
